My lunch hour is rapidly slipping away from me during the institutionalized slavery that is my corporate work day. Yet I could not help myself but take a minute to write about this particular Chipotle along with its all-star team. I must tell you, one MVP stands out in my mind at Chipotle. I do not know her and have never met her in my life. I am not an important person, nor do I dress as though I am a professional. I can see that she is of a different race/ethnicity than me. I can only assume that her background differs from mine. Yet her welcoming demeanor and kind smile is more revitalizing than a Starbucks double shot. There is another Chipotle that is literally 2 steps from where I work in the loop. But I spend what little time I have traversing the several city blocks that separate me from 10 S. LaSalle St. [intersection of LaSalle and Madison St. in Chicago] because the food and the service have never once disappointed me. Being remembered? That is just guac on top of delicious cooked-to-perfection Barbacoa or juicy chef's-special-seeming Carnitas. For those days I am in my vegan phase? Savory beans and vegetables make my day every time. The food has always been excellent to the taste, but the service is what makes the biggest difference. And this individual I am writing about serves her customers like she is the franchise OWNER not an employee or even a manager... Thank you for hiring such an asset of a person, and also for delivering an excellent product.
